Data Exploration

Explore Runtime

1. Total Runtime
1. What is the distribution of runtime (for the whole study)?
2. What are the min, max, mean & SD?
3. Do they follow a normal distribution?

participantData$TOTAL_T_M 
       n  missing distinct     Info     Mean      Gmd      .05      .10      .25      .50      .75      .90      .95 
     338        0      319        1    40.12     9.59    26.51    29.36    34.49    39.28    45.44    51.63    55.24 

lowest : 20.93 21.91 22.03 22.43 22.54, highest: 61.43 61.51 62.56 64.34 66.12

Analysis
The mean total runtime was approximately 40 minutes, with a standard deviation of ~ 9 minutes. The fastest person finished in 21 minutes (suspicious) with the longest taking 66 minutes (also suspicious). A Shapiro-Wilk test for normality yielded a value of W = 0.99, 0.01 < p < 0.05, suggesting that the distibution is significantly non-normal, however, the S-W test is known to be biased toward non-normalcy for large samples. The distribution does appear to be slightly positively skewed. Inspection of the QQ-plot reveals that the distribution can be treated as normal for this sample size.
